    <note type="biography">
        <p>Geographer and map-maker. For many years aided his uncle, Aaron Arrowsmith (<hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>) in the construction of his large collection of maps and charts. Established his own business in 1824. Founding fellow of Royal Geographical Society, 1830; member of the society’s council, 1851–68. Many of his smaller maps appeared in the journals of the Royal Geographical Society.</p></note>
